# IsoForge does NOT use environment variables for API keys.
# Keys are entered by the user in the browser and stored only in sessionStorage.
#
# This file exists only as documentation.
#
# Required API keys (entered at runtime in the UI):
# - Anthropic API Key (Claude Opus 4.5) → https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# - Google AI API Key (Imagen 4 Ultra)  → https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# Optional — Upstash Redis (for persistent item suggestions + generation history):
# Provision via Vercel dashboard → Storage → Create Database → Upstash Redis
# Then link to project → env vars are injected automatically by Vercel.
# For local dev, copy these from the Upstash console:
#
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://your-db.upstash.io
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=your-token-here
